      "span_text": "A kidney was split in two parts; half was fixed for 6 h at 4°C in 4% 0.1 M phosphate buffered (pH 7.4) formaldehyde (Boehringer Ingelheim, Heidelberg, Germany), and the other half was flash-frozen and stored at −80°C. The contralateral kidney was homogenized in 0.25 M sucrose and 3 mM imidazole buffer (pH 7.4) that contained Complete (Roche), in a Potter-Elvehjem tissue homogenizer (Thomas Scientific, Swedsboro, NJ) [CITATION_1] .",
